The Fourier Transform of $f(t)$ is
\begin{align}
F(\omega) &= \int_{-\infty}^{\infty}f(t)e^{-j\omega t} dt \\
&= \int_{-a/2}^{a/2}1 e^{-j\omega t} dt \\
&= -\frac{1}{j\omega} \left. e^{-j\omega t}\right|_{-a/2}^{a/2} \\
&= -\frac{1}{j\omega}\left\{ e^{-j\omega \frac{a}{2}}-e^{j\omega
\frac{a}{2}}\right\} \\
&= -\frac{1}{j\omega}\left\{\cos \frac{\omega a}{2} -j\sin \frac{\omega a}{2}
-\cos\frac{\omega a}{2} -j\sin \frac{\omega a}{2} \right\} \\
&= \frac{2}{\omega} \sin \frac{\omega a}{2} \\
&= a\frac{\sin \frac{\omega a}{2}}{\frac{\omega a}{2}} \\
\intertext{That is}
f(t) &\fpair a\frac{\sin \frac{\omega a}{2}}{\frac{\omega a}{2}}
\end{align}

