\subsection{Shifting in Time}
If $f(t)\fpair F(\omega)$
\begin{equation}
f(t-\alpha)\fpair e^{-j\alpha \omega)} F(\omega) 
\end{equation}
It states that $f(t-\alpha)$ has the same amplitude as $f(t)$ and only differs
in the phase spectrum by $(-\alpha \omega)$. See Figure~\ref{f3-timeshift} for
an example.

